Good news on the auto front.
General Motors says sales of car and light trucks jumped 6.3% in October
compared to the same month last year.
That's a faster rise than expected.
GM expects to build 1.5 million autos this quarter to keep up with
anticipated strong demand.
And Ford motor says October vehicle sales rose 2.4%, in line with analysts'
forecasts.
Ford attributes the rise in part to robust sales of Ford's new 1999 model
super duty F-series pickups.
